ipsecSaMonModule.name: ipsecSaMonModule

revisions.description: Add module compliance requirements. Added common textual conventions. Other minor edits and clarifications.
Group and compliance statements added. OID value under experimental tree added. Authentication algorithm key length values added.

ipsecSaMonModule.contactinfo: Tim Jenkins TimeStep Corporation 362 Terry Fox Drive Kanata, ON K0A 2H0 Canada +1 (613) 599-3610 tjenkins@timestep.com John Shriver Intel Corporation 28 Crosby Drive Bedford, MA 01730 +1 (781) 687-1329 John.Shriver@intel.com
ipsecSaMonModule.description: The MIB module to describe generic IPsec objects, and entity level objects and events for those types.

IpsecSaCreatorIdent.name: IpsecSaCreatorIdent
IpsecSaCreatorIdent.description: A value indicating how an SA was created.

IpsecIpv6Address.name: IpsecIpv6Address
IpsecIpv6Address.description: This data type is used to model IPv6 addresses. This is a binary string of 16 octets in network byte-order. For implementations that do not support IPv6, this address should appear as the 'IPv4-mapped IPv6 address' as defined in Section 2.5.4 of [IPV6AA]. Specifically, the prefix '0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:FFFF::/96' is used for IPv4 addresses.

IpsecRawId.name: IpsecRawId
IpsecRawId.description: This data type is used to model the ID values used by entities that have negotiated and created SAs. The values are taken directly from any payloads exchanged, independent of the type of ID transmitted. In some cases, the payload may be truncated. Note also that some IDs have human readable forms that are not used by this textual convention.

ipsecSaMonitorMIB.name: ipsecSaMonitorMIB
ipsecSaMonitorMIB.description: This is the base object identifier for all IPsec branches.

saTables.name: saTables
saTables.description: This is the base object identifier for all SA tables.

saStatistics.name: saStatistics
saStatistics.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global counters for IPsec security associations.

saErrors.name: saErrors
saErrors.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global error counters for IPsec security associations.

saTraps.name: saTraps
saTraps.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are traps for IPsec security associations.

saTrapObjects.name: saTrapObjects
saTrapObjects.description: This is the base object identifier for objects which are used as part of traps.

saTrapControl.name: saTrapControl
saTrapControl.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are trap controls for IPsec security associations.

saGroups.name: saGroups
saGroups.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which describe the groups in this MIB.

saConformance.name: saConformance
saConformance.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which describe the conformance for this MIB.

ipsecSaEspInTable.name: ipsecSaEspInTable
ipsecSaEspInTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPsec inbound ESP SAs. There should be one row for every inbound ESP security association that exists in the entity. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

ipsecSaEspInEntry.name: ipsecSaEspInEntry
ipsecSaEspInEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular IPsec inbound ESP SA. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

ipsecSaEspInAddress.name: ipsecSaEspInAddress
ipsecSaEspInAddress.description: The destination address of the SA. IPv4 entities will prefix the IP address with '0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:FFFF::'.

ipsecSaEspInSpi.name: ipsecSaEspInSpi
ipsecSaEspInSpi.description: The security parameters index of the SA.

ipsecSaEspInDestId.name: ipsecSaEspInDestId
ipsecSaEspInDestId.description: The destination identifier of the SA. It may be 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during SA creation negotiation.

ipsecSaEspInDestIdType.name: ipsecSaEspInDestIdType
ipsecSaEspInDestIdType.description: The type of identifier presented by 'ipsecSaEspInDestId'. It may be 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation.

ipsecSaEspInSourceId.name: ipsecSaEspInSourceId
ipsecSaEspInSourceId.description: The source identifier of the SA. It may be 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during SA creation negotiation.

ipsecSaEspInSourceIdType.name: ipsecSaEspInSourceIdType
ipsecSaEspInSourceIdType.description: The type of identifier presented by 'ipsecSaEspInSourceId'. It may be 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation.

ipsecSaEspInProtocol.name: ipsecSaEspInProtocol
ipsecSaEspInProtocol.description: The transport-layer protocol number that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any protocol.

ipsecSaEspInDestPort.name: ipsecSaEspInDestPort
ipsecSaEspInDestPort.description: The destination port number of the protocol that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any port number.

ipsecSaEspInSourcePort.name: ipsecSaEspInSourcePort
ipsecSaEspInSourcePort.description: The source port number of the protocol that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any port number.

ipsecSaEspInCreator.name: ipsecSaEspInCreator
ipsecSaEspInCreator.description: The creator of this SA. This MIB makes no assumptions about how the SAs are created. They may be created statically, or by a key exchange protocol such as IKE, or by some other method.

ipsecSaEspInEncapsulation.name: ipsecSaEspInEncapsulation
ipsecSaEspInEncapsulation.description: The type of encapsulation used by this SA.

ipsecSaEspInEncAlg.name: ipsecSaEspInEncAlg
ipsecSaEspInEncAlg.description: A unique value representing the encryption algorithm applied to traffic or 0 if there is no encryption used.

ipsecSaEspInEncKeyLength.name: ipsecSaEspInEncKeyLength
ipsecSaEspInEncKeyLength.description: The length of the encryption key in bits used for the algorithm specified in the 'ipsecSaEspInEncAlg' object. It may be 0 if the key length is implicit in the specified algorithm or there is no encryption specified.

ipsecSaEspInAuthAlg.name: ipsecSaEspInAuthAlg
ipsecSaEspInAuthAlg.description: A unique value representing the hash algorithm applied to traffic or 0 if there is no authentication used.

ipsecSaEspInAuthKeyLength.name: ipsecSaEspInAuthKeyLength
ipsecSaEspInAuthKeyLength.description: The length of the authentication key in bits used for the algorithm specified in the 'ipsecSaEspInAuthAlg'. It may be 0 if the key length is implicit in the specified algorithm or there is no authentication specified.

ipsecSaEspInRepWinSize.name: ipsecSaEspInRepWinSize
ipsecSaEspInRepWinSize.description: The size of the anti-replay window used by this SA, or 0 if anti-replay checking is not being done.

ipsecSaEspInLimitSeconds.name: ipsecSaEspInLimitSeconds
ipsecSaEspInLimitSeconds.description: The maximum lifetime in seconds of the SA, or 0 if there is no time constraint on its expiration. The display value is limited to 4294967295 seconds (more than 136 years); values greater than that value will be truncated.

ipsecSaEspInLimitKbytes.name: ipsecSaEspInLimitKbytes
ipsecSaEspInLimitKbytes.description: The maximum traffic in kilobytes that the SA is allowed to process, or 0 if there is no traffic constraint on its expiration. The display value is limited to 4294967295 kilobytes; values greater than that value will be truncated.

ipsecSaEspInAccSeconds.name: ipsecSaEspInAccSeconds
ipsecSaEspInAccSeconds.description: The number of seconds accumulated against the SA's expiration by time. This is also the number of seconds that the SA has existed.

ipsecSaEspInAccKbytes.name: ipsecSaEspInAccKbytes
ipsecSaEspInAccKbytes.description: The amount of traffic accumulated that counts against the SA's expiration by traffic limitation, measured in kilobytes. This value may be 0 if the SA does not expire based on traffic.

ipsecSaEspInUserOctets.name: ipsecSaEspInUserOctets
ipsecSaEspInUserOctets.description: The amount of user level traffic measured in bytes handled by the SA. This is the number of bytes of the decrypted IP packet, including the original IP header of that decrypted packet. This is not necessarily the same as the amount of traffic applied against the traffic expiration limit due to padding or other protocol specific overhead.

ipsecSaEspInPackets.name: ipsecSaEspInPackets
ipsecSaEspInPackets.description: The number of packets handled by the SA.

ipsecSaEspInDecryptErrors.name: ipsecSaEspInDecryptErrors
ipsecSaEspInDecryptErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to detectable decryption errors. Not all decryption errors are detectable within SA processing, so this count should not be considered definitive.

ipsecSaEspInAuthErrors.name: ipsecSaEspInAuthErrors
ipsecSaEspInAuthErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to authentication errors.

ipsecSaEspInReplayErrors.name: ipsecSaEspInReplayErrors
ipsecSaEspInReplayErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to replay errors.

ipsecSaEspInPolicyErrors.name: ipsecSaEspInPolicyErrors
ipsecSaEspInPolicyErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to policy errors. This includes packets where the next protocol is invalid.

ipsecSaEspInPadErrors.name: ipsecSaEspInPadErrors
ipsecSaEspInPadErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to pad value errors. Implementations that do not check this must not support this object.

ipsecSaEspInOtherReceiveErrors.name: ipsecSaEspInOtherReceiveErrors
ipsecSaEspInOtherReceiveErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to errors other than decryption, authentication, replay errors or, when supported, invalid padding errors. This may include packets dropped due to a lack of receive buffers, and may include packets dropped due to congestion at the decryption element.

ipsecSaAhInAccKbytes.name: ipsecSaAhInAccKbytes

ipsecSaAhInUserOctets.name: ipsecSaAhInUserOctets
ipsecSaAhInUserOctets.description: The amount of user level traffic measured in bytes handled by the SA. This is the number of bytes of the de-processed IP packet, including the original IP header of that de- processed packet. This is not necessarily the same as the amount of traffic applied against the traffic expiration limit due to padding or other protocol specific overhead.

ipsecSaAhInPackets.name: ipsecSaAhInPackets
ipsecSaAhInPackets.description: The number of packets handled by the SA.

ipsecSaAhInAuthErrors.name: ipsecSaAhInAuthErrors

ipsecSaAhInReplayErrors.name: ipsecSaAhInReplayErrors

ipsecSaAhInPolicyErrors.name: ipsecSaAhInPolicyErrors

ipsecSaAhInOtherReceiveErrors.name: ipsecSaAhInOtherReceiveErrors
ipsecSaAhInOtherReceiveErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to errors other than decryption, authentication or replay errors. This may include packets dropped due to a lack of receive buffers, and may include packets dropped due to congestion at the authentication element.

ipsecSaIpcompInCpi.name: ipsecSaIpcompInCpi
ipsecSaIpcompInCpi.description: The CPI of the SA. Since the lower values of CPIs are reserved to be the same as the algorithm, the syntax for this object is the same as the transform.

ipsecSaIpcompInDestId.name: ipsecSaIpcompInDestId
ipsecSaIpcompInDestId.description: The destination identifier of the SA. It may be 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode, or 0 if this SA is used with multiple SAs in security association suites. This value, if non-zero, is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during SA creation negotiation, or the equivalent process.

ipsecSaIpcompInDestIdType.name: ipsecSaIpcompInDestIdType
ipsecSaIpcompInDestIdType.description: The type of identifier presented by 'ipsecSaIpcompInDestId'. It may be 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode, or if this SA is used with multiple SAs in security association suites.

ipsecSaIpcompInEncapsulation.description: The type of encapsulation used by this SA.

ipsecSaIpcompInDecompAlg.name: ipsecSaIpcompInDecompAlg
ipsecSaIpcompInDecompAlg.description: A unique value representing the decompression algorithm applied to traffic.

ipsecSaIpcompInSeconds.name: ipsecSaIpcompInSeconds
ipsecSaIpcompInSeconds.description: The number of seconds that the SA has existed.

ipsecSaIpcompInUserOctets.name: ipsecSaIpcompInUserOctets
ipsecSaIpcompInUserOctets.description: The amount of user level traffic measured in bytes handled by the SA. This is the number of bytes of the uncompressed IP packet, including the original IP header of that uncompressed packet. Packets which are not decompressed by the SA are not counted in this total.

ipsecSaIpcompInPackets.name: ipsecSaIpcompInPackets

ipsecSaIpcompInOtherReceiveErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to errors other than decompression errors. This may include packets dropped due to a lack of receive buffers, and packets dropped due to congestion at the decompression element.

ipsecSaAhOutAuthAlg.name: ipsecSaAhOutAuthAlg
ipsecSaAhOutAuthAlg.description: A unique value representing the hash algorithm applied to traffic carried by this SA.

ipsecSaAhOutAuthKeyLength.name: ipsecSaAhOutAuthKeyLength
ipsecSaAhOutAuthKeyLength.description: The length of the authentication key in bits used for the algorithm specified in the 'ipsecSaAhOutAuthAlg' object. It may be 0 if the key length is implicit in the specified algorithm.

ipsecSaAhOutLimitSeconds.name: ipsecSaAhOutLimitSeconds
ipsecSaAhOutLimitSeconds.description: The maximum lifetime in seconds of the SA, or 0 if there is no time constraint on its expiration. The display value is limited to 4294967295 seconds (more than 136 years); values greater than that value will be truncated.

ipsecSaAhOutLimitKbytes.name: ipsecSaAhOutLimitKbytes
ipsecSaAhOutLimitKbytes.description: The maximum traffic in bytes that the SA is allowed to process, or 0 if there is no traffic constraint on its expiration. The display value is limited to 4294967295 kilobytes; values greater than that value will be truncated.

ipsecSaAhOutAccSeconds.name: ipsecSaAhOutAccSeconds
ipsecSaAhOutAccSeconds.description: The number of seconds accumulated against the SA's expiration by time. This is also the number of seconds that the SA has existed.

ipsecSaAhOutAccKbytes.name: ipsecSaAhOutAccKbytes
ipsecSaAhOutAccKbytes.description: The amount of traffic accumulated that counts against the SA's expiration by traffic limitation, measured in kilobytes. This value may be 0 if the SA does not expire based on traffic.

ipsecSaAhOutUserOctets.name: ipsecSaAhOutUserOctets
ipsecSaAhOutUserOctets.description: The amount of user level traffic measured in bytes handled by the SA. This is the number of bytes of the unprocessed IP packet, including the original IP header of that unprocessed packet. This is not necessarily the same as the amount of traffic applied against the traffic expiration limit due to padding or other protocol specific overhead.

ipsecSaAhOutPackets.name: ipsecSaAhOutPackets
ipsecSaAhOutPackets.description: The number of packets handled by the SA.

ipsecSaAhOutSendErrors.name: ipsecSaAhOutSendErrors
ipsecSaAhOutSendErrors.description: The number of packets discarded by the SA due to any error. This may include errors due to a lack of transmit buffers.

ipsecSaIpcompOutTable.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutTable
ipsecSaIpcompOutTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPsec Outbound IPcomp SAs. There should be one row for every outbound IPcomp (security) association that exists in the entity. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

ipsecSaIpcompOutEntry.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutEntry
ipsecSaIpcompOutEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular IPsec Outbound IPcomp SA. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

ipsecSaIpcompOutAddress.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutAddress
ipsecSaIpcompOutAddress.description: The destination address of the SA. If the IPcomp SA is shared across multiple SAs in security association suites, this value may be 0. IPv4 entities will prefix the IP address with '0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:FFFF::'.

ipsecSaIpcompOutCpi.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutCpi
ipsecSaIpcompOutCpi.description: The CPI of the SA. Since the lower values of CPIs are reserved to be the same as the algorithm, the syntax for this object is the same as the transform.

ipsecSaIpcompOutSourceId.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutSourceId
ipsecSaIpcompOutSourceId.description: The source identifier of the SA. It may be 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation, or if this SA is used with multiple SAs in security association suites. This value, if non-zero, is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchange during phase 2 negotiations or the equivalent process.

ipsecSaIpcompOutSourceIdType.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutSourceIdType
ipsecSaIpcompOutSourceIdType.description: The type of identifier presented by 'ipsecSaIpcompOutSourceId'. It may be 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation, or if this SA is used with multiple SAs in security association suites.

ipsecSaIpcompOutDestId.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutDestId
ipsecSaIpcompOutDestId.description: The destination identifier of the SA. It may be 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation, or if this SA is used with multiple SAs in security association suites. This value, if non-zero, is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchange during phase 2 negotiations or the equivalent process.

ipsecSaIpcompOutDestIdType.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutDestIdType
ipsecSaIpcompOutDestIdType.description: The type of identifier presented by 'ipsecSaIpcompOutDestId', or 0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation, or 0 if this SA is used with multiple SAs in security association suites.

ipsecSaIpcompOutProtocol.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutProtocol
ipsecSaIpcompOutProtocol.description: The transport-layer protocol number that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any protocol.

ipsecSaIpcompOutSourcePort.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutSourcePort
ipsecSaIpcompOutSourcePort.description: The source port number of the protocol that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any port number.

ipsecSaIpcompOutDestPort.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutDestPort
ipsecSaIpcompOutDestPort.description: The destination port number of the protocol that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any port number.

ipsecSaIpcompOutCreator.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutCreator
ipsecSaIpcompOutCreator.description: The creator of this SA. This MIB makes no assumptions about how the SAs are created. They may be created statically, or by a key exchange protocol such as IKE, or by some other method.

ipsecSaIpcompOutEncapsulation.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutEncapsulation
ipsecSaIpcompOutEncapsulation.description: The type of encapsulation used by this SA.

ipsecSaIpcompOutCompAlg.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutCompAlg
ipsecSaIpcompOutCompAlg.description: A unique value representing the compression algorithm applied to traffic.

ipsecSaIpcompOutSeconds.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutSeconds
ipsecSaIpcompOutSeconds.description: The number of seconds that the SA has existed.

ipsecSaIpcompOutUserOctets.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutUserOctets
ipsecSaIpcompOutUserOctets.description: The amount of user level traffic measured in bytes handled by the SA. This is the number of bytes of the decompressed IP packet, including the original IP header of that decompressed packet.

ipsecSaIpcompOutOutputOctets.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutOutputOctets
ipsecSaIpcompOutOutputOctets.description: The amount of traffic measured in bytes output by the SA. This includes byte counts from packets compressed by the SA and also packets not modified by the SA. This object can be divided into the 'ipsecSaIpcompOutUserOctets' object to get a compression performance metric for the SA.

ipsecSaIpcompOutPackets.name: ipsecSaIpcompOutPackets
ipsecSaIpcompOutPackets.description: The number of packets handled by the SA. This includes packets that were both compressed and not compressed.

ipsecEspCurrentInboundSAs.name: ipsecEspCurrentInboundSAs
ipsecEspCurrentInboundSAs.description: The current number of inbound ESP SAs in the entity.

ipsecEspTotalInboundSAs.name: ipsecEspTotalInboundSAs
ipsecEspTotalInboundSAs.description: The total number of inbound ESP SAs created in the entity since boot time.

ipsecEspCurrentOutboundSAs.name: ipsecEspCurrentOutboundSAs
ipsecEspCurrentOutboundSAs.description: The current number of outbound ESP SAs in the entity.

ipsecEspTotalOutboundSAs.name: ipsecEspTotalOutboundSAs
ipsecEspTotalOutboundSAs.description: The total number of outbound ESP SAs created in the entity since boot time.

ipsecAhCurrentInboundSAs.name: ipsecAhCurrentInboundSAs
ipsecAhCurrentInboundSAs.description: The current number of inbound AH SAs in the entity.

ipsecAhTotalInboundSAs.name: ipsecAhTotalInboundSAs
ipsecAhTotalInboundSAs.description: The total number of inbound AH SAs created in the entity since boot time.

ipsecAhCurrentOutboundSAs.name: ipsecAhCurrentOutboundSAs
ipsecAhCurrentOutboundSAs.description: The current number of outbound AH SAs in the entity.

ipsecAhTotalOutboundSAs.name: ipsecAhTotalOutboundSAs
ipsecAhTotalOutboundSAs.description: The total number of outbound AH SAs created in the entity since boot time.

ipsecIpcompCurrentInboundSAs.name: ipsecIpcompCurrentInboundSAs
ipsecIpcompCurrentInboundSAs.description: The current number of inbound IPcomp SAs in the entity.

ipsecIpcompTotalInboundSAs.name: ipsecIpcompTotalInboundSAs
ipsecIpcompTotalInboundSAs.description: The total number of inbound IPcomp SAs created in the entity since boot time.

ipsecIpcompCurrentOutboundSAs.name: ipsecIpcompCurrentOutboundSAs
ipsecIpcompCurrentOutboundSAs.description: The current number of outbound IPcomp SAs in the entity.

ipsecIpcompTotalOutboundSAs.name: ipsecIpcompTotalOutboundSAs
ipsecIpcompTotalOutboundSAs.description: The total number of outbound IPcomp SAs created in the entity since boot time.

ipsecDecryptionErrors.name: ipsecDecryptionErrors
ipsecDecryptionErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in SAs since boot time with detectable decryption errors. Not all decryption errors are detectable within SA processing, so this count should not be considered definitive.

ipsecAuthenticationErrors.name: ipsecAuthenticationErrors
ipsecAuthenticationErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in SAs since boot time with authentication errors. This includes all packets in which the hash value is determined to be invalid, for both ESP and AH SAs.

ipsecReplayErrors.name: ipsecReplayErrors
ipsecReplayErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in SAs since boot time with replay errors.

ipsecPolicyErrors.name: ipsecPolicyErrors
ipsecPolicyErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in SAs since boot time and discarded due to policy errors. This includes packets that had selectors that were invalid for the SA that carried them, and also includes packets that arrived at the entity in the clear and that should have been protected by IPsec or should have been dropped.

ipsecOtherReceiveErrors.name: ipsecOtherReceiveErrors
ipsecOtherReceiveErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity in SAs since boot time and discarded due to errors not due to decryption, authentication, replay or policy.

ipsecSendErrors.name: ipsecSendErrors
ipsecSendErrors.description: The total number of packets to be sent by the entity in SAs since boot time and discarded due to errors.

ipsecUnknownSpiErrors.name: ipsecUnknownSpiErrors
ipsecUnknownSpiErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity since boot time with SPIs or CPIs that were not valid.

ipsecSecurityProtocol.name: ipsecSecurityProtocol
ipsecSecurityProtocol.description: A security protocol associated with the trap.

ipsecSPI.name: ipsecSPI
ipsecSPI.description: An SPI associated with a trap. Where the security protocol associated with the trap is IPcomp, this value has a maximum of 65535.

ipsecLocalAddress.name: ipsecLocalAddress
ipsecLocalAddress.description: A local IP address associated with the trap. IPv4 entities will prefix the IP address with '0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:FFFF::'.

ipsecPeerAddress.name: ipsecPeerAddress
ipsecPeerAddress.description: A peer IP address associated with the trap. IPv4 entities will prefix the IP address with '0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:FFFF::'.

espAuthFailureTrapEnable.name: espAuthFailureTrapEnable
espAuthFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether espAuthFailureTrap traps should be generated.

ahAuthFailureTrapEnable.name: ahAuthFailureTrapEnable
ahAuthFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether ahAuthFailureTrap traps should be generated.

espReplayFailureTrapEnable.name: espReplayFailureTrapEnable
espReplayFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether espReplayFailureTrap traps should be generated.

ahReplayFailureTrapEnable.name: ahReplayFailureTrapEnable
ahReplayFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether ahReplayFailureTrap traps should be generated.

espPolicyFailureTrapEnable.name: espPolicyFailureTrapEnable
espPolicyFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether espPolicyFailureTrap traps should be generated.

ahPolicyFailureTrapEnable.name: ahPolicyFailureTrapEnable
ahPolicyFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether ahPolicyFailureTrap traps should be generated.

invalidSpiTrapEnable.name: invalidSpiTrapEnable
invalidSpiTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether invalidSpiTrap traps should be generated.

otherPolicyFailureTrapEnable.name: otherPolicyFailureTrapEnable
otherPolicyFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether otherPolicyFailureTrap traps should be generated.

espAuthFailureTrap.name: espAuthFailureTrap
espAuthFailureTrap.description: IPsec packets with invalid hashes were found in an inbound ESP SA. The total number of authentication errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the 'ipsecSaEspInTable' table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

ahAuthFailureTrap.name: ahAuthFailureTrap
ahAuthFailureTrap.description: IPsec packets with invalid hashes were found in an inbound AH SA. The total number of authentication errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the 'ipsecSaAhInTable' table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

espReplayFailureTrap.name: espReplayFailureTrap
espReplayFailureTrap.description: IPsec packets with invalid sequence numbers were found in an inbound ESP SA. The total number of replay errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the 'ipsecSaEspInTable' table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

ahReplayFailureTrap.name: ahReplayFailureTrap
ahReplayFailureTrap.description: IPsec packets with invalid sequence numbers were found in the specified AH SA. The total number of replay errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the 'ipsecSaAhInTable' table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

espPolicyFailureTrap.name: espPolicyFailureTrap
espPolicyFailureTrap.description: IPsec packets carrying packets with invalid selectors for the specified ESP SA were found. The total number of policy errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the 'ipsecSaEspInTable' table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

ahPolicyFailureTrap.name: ahPolicyFailureTrap
ahPolicyFailureTrap.description: IPsec packets carrying packets with invalid selectors for the specified AH SA were found. The total number of policy errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the 'ipsecSaAhInTable' table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

espInvalidSpiTrap.name: espInvalidSpiTrap
espInvalidSpiTrap.description: A packet with an unknown SPI was detected from the specified peer with the specified SPI using the specified protocol. The destination address of the received packet is specified by 'ipsecLocalAddress'. The value 'ifIndex' may be 0 if this optional linkage is unsupported. If the object 'ipsecSecurityProtocol' has the value for IPcomp, then the 'ipsecSPI' object is the CPI of the packet. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per peer (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

otherPolicyFailureTrap.name: otherPolicyFailureTrap
otherPolicyFailureTrap.description: Clear packets were found that should not have been sent to the entity in the clear. The total number of policy errors accumulated by the entity is sent, along with the source and destination addresses of the packet that triggered the trap. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per source address pair (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

ipsecSaEspGroup.name: ipsecSaEspGroup
ipsecSaEspGroup.description: A collection of objects that describe the state of the security associations of the ESP protocol.

ipsecSaAhGroup.name: ipsecSaAhGroup
ipsecSaAhGroup.description: A collection of objects that describe the state of the security associations of the AH protocol.

ipsecSaIpcompGroup.name: ipsecSaIpcompGroup
ipsecSaIpcompGroup.description: A collection of objects that describe the state of the security associations of the IPComp protocol.

ipsecSaErrorsGroup.name: ipsecSaErrorsGroup
ipsecSaErrorsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing global IPsec error counters.

ipsecSaFailureTrapEnableGroup.name: ipsecSaFailureTrapEnableGroup
ipsecSaFailureTrapEnableGroup.description: A collection of objects providing control over trap generation.

ipsecSaTrapArgumentGroup.name: ipsecSaTrapArgumentGroup
ipsecSaTrapArgumentGroup.description: A collection of objects used only as arguments in traps.

ipsecSaMonitorCompliance.name: ipsecSaMonitorCompliance
ipsecSaMonitorCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities which implement the IPsec Monitoring MIB.
